@ThinkingandTinkering you're absolutely correct,  I'm asking questions because I know that my comprehension and understanding is limited, I don't have the answers but I don't dismiss others ideas and attempts simply because I can't comprehend them based on my limited knowledge. 

A more recent example is how 'society' couldn't comprehend heavier-than-air flying machines, it wasn't until the Wright Brothers studied aerodynamics and built planes (many of the first models failed) that we as a species understood 'flight'..

What if, what we currently refer to as "free energy" devices that seemingly fail are like the first attempts at flying? What if we, in our arrogant surety, can not comprehend a source of energy that we can not currently measure/make use of .
